    "Q6. What is a complex number in mathematics, and how is it represented in Python?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "5c0573dc-3348-4d16-a79a-dbb584c65a9d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "Ans-A complex number is a number that comprises both a real part and an imaginary part. In Python, complex numbers are represented using the j or J suffix for the imaginary part.\n",
    "\n",
    "Example:\n",
    "z = 3 + 2j  # 3 is the real part, 2j is the imaginary part"
   ]
